# .env — COLLECTOR NODE CONFIGURATION
# Copy to .env and fill in before running docker compose up.
# One copy per node. Do NOT commit .env — it has node-specific addressing.
#
# Keys are managed two ways:
#   - You set the REQUIRED / OPTIONAL keys below by hand.
#   - `make` targets upsert tool-owned keys (NODE_NAME) in place via
#     scripts/envset.sh — never blindly appended, so this file does not
#     drift. Run `make check-env` to spot missing keys.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# IP or hostname of the aggregator node (runs the broker stack).
# Use a stable address — WireGuard or LAN IP recommended over DNS.
# Example: 10.10.30.10
AGGREGATOR_HOST=10.0.0.x

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL — defaults shown, override only if you have port conflicts
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Node-exporter port on this host.
# Change if something else is already bound to 9100.
#NODE_EXPORTER_PORT=9100

# Aggregator Prometheus remote_write port.
#AGGREGATOR_PROM_PORT=9090

# Aggregator Loki push port.
#AGGREGATOR_LOKI_PORT=3100

# Docker inventory exporter port.
# Change if something else is already bound to 9338.
#INVENTORY_PORT=9338

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TOOL-MANAGED — set automatically; listed here for documentation only
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Label applied to all metrics and logs from this node.
# `make` stamps this from the system hostname if you leave it unset.
#NODE_NAME=node-01

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# KUBERNETES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Not configured here. A cluster is ingested by the aggregator as a pull target
# (aggregator/config/prometheus.yml); the collector stays k8s-free.
